articles.author: Tetsushi Kajimoto
articles.description: Japanese exports grew for a second straight month in October but at a sharply slower pace due to slumping China-bound shipments of chips and steel, as weakening external demand takes its toll on the trade-reliant economy.
articles.title: Japan's export growth slows as China, global downturn risks loom

articles.author: Svea Herbst-Bayliss
articles.description: ValueAct Capital has built a large stake in Walt Disney (DIS.N) and sees room for the media and entertainment giant's stock price to roughly double, people familiar with the investment firm's thinking said on Wednesday.
articles.title: ValueAct builds stake in Disney, adds drama at home of Mickey Mouse -sources

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Hyundai Motor (005380.KS) unveiled its first high-performance electric vehicle(EV), an N sport variant of its IONIQ 5 crossover SUV.
articles.title: Hyundai unveils its first high-performance electric car

articles.author: Wayne Cole
articles.description: Australia employment rebounded strongly in October, after a soft patch the previous month, though the jobless rate still ticked higher as more people went looking for work and rapid migration boosted the supply of labour.
articles.title: Australia employment rebounds in Oct, jobless rate still edges up

articles.author: Josh Ye
articles.description: Chinese technology giant Tencent Holdings (0700.HK) on Wednesday said it has a large stockpile of AI chips from U.S. maker Nvidia (NVDA.O), but that broadened U.S. restrictions on high-end chip sales to China will eventually impact its cloud services.
articles.title: Tencent says has Nvidia AI chip stockpile but seeking to buy domestic

articles.author: David Shepardson
articles.description: General Motors' (GM.N) tentative labor deal with the United Auto Workers (UAW) union closed in on ratification as the votes were counted on Wednesday.
articles.title: GM's labor deal with UAW union on verge of ratification

articles.author: Stephen Nellis
articles.description: Microsoft (MSFT.O) on Wednesday announced a duo of custom-designed computing chips, joining other big tech firms that - faced with the high cost of delivering artificial intelligence services - are bringing key technologies in-house.
articles.title: Microsoft introduces its own chips for AI, with eye on cost

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden meets Chinese leader Xi Jinping for the first time in a year on Wednesday, for talks that may ease friction between the adversarial superpowers on military conflicts, drug-trafficking and artificial intelligence.
articles.title: Biden, Xi meet as US-China military, economic tensions grind on

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Emily Rose
articles.description: Israel said its forces were operating in and around Gaza's biggest hospital, a chief objective in its campaign to destroy Palestinian Hamas militants that the army says stored weapons and ran a command centre in tunnels beneath the buildings.
articles.title: Israeli troops deepen search at main Gaza hospital for evidence of Hamas

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Vatican has confirmed a ban on Catholics becoming Freemasons, a centuries-old secretive society that the Catholic Church has long viewed with hostility and has an estimated global membership of up to six million.
articles.title: Vatican confirms ban on Catholics becoming Freemasons
